## 总控Prompt（整段复制进Claude Code）

```
You are executing an autonomous build of PulseCity, a city intelligence demo.

INPUTS:
- PulseCity_VibeCoding_Guide_v2.md — the full implementation spec
- MASTER_PROMPT.md — this file, containing phase definitions and acceptance criteria

OPERATING RULES (read carefully, these override your defaults):
1. NEVER ask me questions. Every decision point is covered by the guide;
   if genuinely ambiguous, choose the simpler option and log it in DECISIONS.md.
2. Skip ALL v0.dev sections in the guide. Build the UI yourself following
   the design system in the guide (dark theme #0a0a0f, category colors,
   Inter font, flat design, Bloomberg-Terminal-meets-Citizen aesthetic).
3. Execute phases STRICTLY in order. A phase is complete ONLY when ALL its
   acceptance criteria pass. Do not start the next phase early.
4. After each phase: run the verification commands, then append a status
   line to PROGRESS.md: "[timestamp] Phase N: PASS/FAIL — notes".
5. On failure: attempt fixes up to 3 times per phase. If still failing
   after 3 attempts, apply the phase's FALLBACK rule, log it, and continue.
   Never stop the whole run because of one phase.
6. If .env.local is missing REDDIT_CLIENT_ID: skip Phase 5 entirely,
   set the events API to mock-only mode, log this in DECISIONS.md.
7. Keep a running DECISIONS.md documenting every judgment call you made.
8. Final deliverable: working `npm run dev`, plus a FINAL_REPORT.md.

Now read both md files fully, then begin Phase 0.

================ PHASE DEFINITIONS ================

--- PHASE 0: Environment & Scaffold ---
Tasks: Guide's Claude Code Prompt 1 (init Next.js 14 + deps + structure
+ CLAUDE.md creation as specified in guide section 1).
Acceptance criteria:
  AC-0.1: `npm run build` exits 0 on the empty scaffold
  AC-0.2: CLAUDE.md exists at project root with the content from guide section 1
  AC-0.3: 'mapbox-gl/dist/mapbox-gl.css' is imported in app/layout.tsx
  AC-0.4: .env.example exists listing all 4 keys
Verification: npm run build && test -f CLAUDE.md && grep -q "mapbox-gl.*css" app/layout.tsx
Fallback: none — this phase must pass; if create-next-app fails 3 times,
report the raw error in PROGRESS.md and STOP (only phase allowed to stop the run).

--- PHASE 1: Types & Mock Data ---
Tasks: Guide Prompt 2 (lib/types.ts + lib/mock-data.ts).
Acceptance criteria:
  AC-1.1: `npx tsc --noEmit` exits 0
  AC-1.2: zero occurrences of `: any` in lib/types.ts
  AC-1.3: SEATTLE_POIS has exactly 30 entries; SEATTLE_EVENTS has 12;
          exactly 3 events have status 'predicted'
  AC-1.4: every lat is between 47.5–47.75 and every lng between -122.45–-122.2
          (write a quick node script to assert this, run it, then delete it)
  AC-1.5: all createdAt timestamps parse as valid ISO dates within last 24h
Verification: tsc check + the assertion script
Fallback: if coordinate validation keeps failing, regenerate coordinates
from a hardcoded list of 30 verified Seattle locations.

--- PHASE 2: City Tools + Chat API (THE CORE) ---
Tasks: Guide Prompts 3 + 4 (lib/city-tools.ts, app/api/chat/route.ts,
lib/chat-client.ts). Model: claude-sonnet-4-6, SSE streaming, agentic
tool-use loop capped at 5 iterations.
Acceptance criteria:
  AC-2.1: `npm run build` exits 0
  AC-2.2: write scripts/test-chat.mjs that POSTs
          {"messages":[{"role":"user","content":"What's happening near Capitol Hill?"}]}
          to localhost:3000/api/chat and parses the SSE stream.
          Assert ALL of: at least one 'tool_call' event received,
          at least one 'text_delta' event received,
          exactly one 'done' event received, no 'error' events.
          (Start dev server in background for the test, kill it after.)
  AC-2.3: same script with query "Find me dinner not near any events"
          must trigger a query_poi tool call with exclude_near_events
          visible in server logs, and 'done' event must contain at least
          one referencedPoi
  AC-2.4: executeTool returns compact JSON — verify search_events output
          for the full event list is under 2000 characters
  AC-2.5: grep confirms ANTHROPIC_API_KEY appears only in app/api/** and lib
          files imported solely by API routes, never in any 'use client' file
Verification: build + run scripts/test-chat.mjs twice (two queries)
Fallback: if SSE streaming fails persistently, downgrade to non-streamed
JSON responses (single response object), keep the tool_call status events
as a synthetic pre-response payload, and log the downgrade. The tool-use
loop itself must NOT be cut — it is the demo's core.

--- PHASE 3: UI Components (replacing v0) ---
Tasks: Build MapView, EventFeed, ChatPanel, EventDetailDrawer,
ToolCallIndicator, PredictionCard per guide sections 2 (visual specs)
and 4.1 (wiring spec). Plus app/api/events/route.ts + lib/geo-utils.ts
(guide Prompt 6) and lib/prediction-engine.ts (guide Prompt 7).
Acceptance criteria:
  AC-3.1: `npm run build` exits 0
  AC-3.2: /api/events returns valid JSON array with >= 12 events,
          each having a distanceMiles field when lat/lng params provided
  AC-3.3: app/page.tsx renders MapView + EventFeed + ChatPanel in the
          60/40 split layout; map components have 'use client'
  AC-3.4: ChatPanel uses streamCityChat callbacks; ToolCallIndicator
          appears in the component tree wired to onToolCall/onToolDone
  AC-3.5: predicted events render with dashed border class and a
          PREDICTED badge (grep the component for both)
  AC-3.6: clicking a POI chip in chat calls the highlight callback that
          reaches MapView's highlightedPois prop (verify the prop chain
          exists in page.tsx by reading the code)
Verification: build + curl /api/events + code inspection of prop wiring
Fallback: if Mapbox heatmap layer causes issues, ship markers-only and
log it. If react-map-gl version conflicts arise, pin to a known-good
version rather than fighting the latest.

--- PHASE 4: Map-Chat Integration Test ---
Tasks: end-to-end wiring validation and fixes.
Acceptance criteria:
  AC-4.1: extend scripts/test-chat.mjs — the 'done' event's
          referencedPois entries must each have valid lat/lng that
          exist in SEATTLE_POIS
  AC-4.2: selectedEvent state flows: EventFeed click → page state →
          MapView impact-radius circle AND EventDetailDrawer open
          (verify by code reading; document the chain in PROGRESS.md)
  AC-4.3: dev server runs 60 seconds with zero unhandled errors in
          console while test script fires 3 chat queries
Verification: run the extended script against dev server
Fallback: none needed — fix until passing or 3 attempts then log
remaining issues as KNOWN_ISSUES section in FINAL_REPORT.md.

--- PHASE 5: Reddit + Haiku Classification (SKIP if no Reddit creds) ---
Tasks: Guide Prompt 5 (reddit-client.ts, classify-events.ts using
claude-haiku-4-5 batched classification, /api/reddit route).
Acceptance criteria:
  AC-5.1: `npm run build` exits 0
  AC-5.2: /api/reddit returns within 5 seconds and ALWAYS includes the
          12 mock events even if Reddit fetch fails (test by temporarily
          setting an invalid Reddit credential and confirming graceful
          fallback — then restore)
  AC-5.3: classify-events makes exactly ONE Anthropic call per batch
          (not per post) — verify by code inspection
  AC-5.4: events with unmatched location_mention are dropped, never
          given fake coordinates (code inspection)
Verification: build + timed curl of /api/reddit + fault-injection test
Fallback: on persistent Reddit OAuth failure, hard-disable the Reddit
path (return mock only), log it. The demo must never depend on Reddit.

--- PHASE 6: Polish — Animations, Realtime Sim, Responsive ---
Tasks: Guide v1 Prompts 10, 11, 13 (referenced from v2 sections 4.2/4.3):
pulse-ring keyframes, fade-in-up, typing dots, drawer transitions,
useRealtimeEvents/useCityPulse/useBreakingAlert hooks, tablet/mobile
breakpoints.
Acceptance criteria:
  AC-6.1: `npm run build` exits 0
  AC-6.2: globals.css (or animations.css) contains keyframes:
          pulse-ring, fade-in-up, typing-dot (grep)
  AC-6.3: useRealtimeEvents hook exists and is consumed in page.tsx
  AC-6.4: map container has explicit height at every breakpoint
          (grep for h-[ or height in the responsive classes)
Verification: build + grep checks
Fallback: responsive layout is the FIRST thing to cut if over budget —
desktop-only is acceptable for the demo. Animations on map bubbles and
the ToolCallIndicator are NOT cuttable.

--- PHASE 7: Final Build + Report ---
Tasks: guide Prompt 12 checks + write FINAL_REPORT.md.
Acceptance criteria:
  AC-7.1: clean `npm run build` from scratch (rm -rf .next first) exits 0
  AC-7.2: `npm run dev` starts and serves the page (curl localhost:3000
          returns 200 with "PulseCity" in the HTML)
  AC-7.3: FINAL_REPORT.md exists with sections:
          - What was built (per phase, one line each)
          - DECISIONS.md summary (top 5 judgment calls)
          - KNOWN_ISSUES (anything that hit fallback rules)
          - What needs human attention (visual polish items you could
            not self-evaluate: animation timing, color feel, demo wow)
          - Exact commands to run the demo
Verification: the three checks above
Fallback: none — report honestly whatever state the project is in.

================ END PHASE DEFINITIONS ================

Begin now. Read both md files, then start Phase 0.
```

